; Regression test for issue #1092: balance assignments were evaluated in file
; (parse) order rather than transaction date order.
;
; When a later-dated transaction appears before a balance assignment in the
; ledger file, the balance assignment should compute the posting amount based
; on the account balance as of its own transaction date — ignoring any
; transactions with a later date, even if those appear earlier in the file.
;
; In this example the July 20 transfer appears first in the file, but the
; July 10 balance assignment must treat Liabilities:Test as having a zero
; balance at that date (not -$30.00 from the later-dated transfer).  The
; correct final balance of Liabilities:Test is therefore -$230.00 (the
; assignment sets it to -$200 on July 10, then the transfer adds another
; -$30 on July 20), not -$200.00 (which would result from using the file-
; order running balance of -$30 when computing the assignment amount).

2020/07/20 Transfer
    Expenses:Misc              $30.00
    Liabilities:Test

2020/07/10 Opening Balance
    Liabilities:Test                      = $-200.00
    Equity:Opening Balances

test bal
             $200.00  Equity:Opening Balances
              $30.00  Expenses:Misc
            $-230.00  Liabilities:Test
--------------------
                   0
end test
